message.content:
cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with extensions of Linear Temporal Logic (LTL) and its parameterized versions.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses algorithmic properties of the logics and their applications in solving games.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper introduces a new parameterized logic with costs, which can be used in programming language semantics.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses omega-regular properties expressible in the logics.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses algorithmic properties of the logics and their complexity.
